---
interface Props {
  brandYaml: string;
  voicePreview: string;
}
const { brandYaml, voicePreview } = Astro.props as Props;
---
<section id="thesis" class="section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="idx">§ 01 · Why it matters</div>
      <h2>Brand is <em>more</em> valuable in the agentic age, not less.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="idx-grid" style="margin-top:56px">
      <div class="section-idx">01.1</div>
      <p class="lede">
        Most companies will get this <span class="strike">wrong</span>. They'll treat brand as a cost center to automate past. They'll save on headcount and discover, two years in, that their agents are producing copy in a voice that isn't theirs, media buys that miss their positioning, and ChatGPT describing them to customers using words they'd never put in writing.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="idx-grid" style="margin-top:56px">
      <div class="section-idx">01.2</div>
      <div class="body-text">
        <p>The knowledge that makes your brand distinctive lives in senior marketers' heads. The judgment calls. The <i>'we don't say it that way.'</i> The instinct for what's on-brand at the edge. That's the value a brand consultancy has always sold. It's also the value agents can't access.</p>
        <p>When your marketing team is half agents, your own and your vendors', brand fidelity stops being a guidelines problem. It becomes an infrastructure problem. Every agent in the stack needs a version of that senior strategist's judgment, on call, in a form they can read.</p>
        <p>That's what Encoded builds. We encode the tacit work of brand into a file every agent reads before it acts. Authored once. Consumed everywhere. <b>Brand-led. Technically rigorous. Open standard.</b></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="idx-grid pull-quote" style="margin-top:64px">
      <div class="section-idx">The thought</div>
      <div>
        <blockquote>In the world of agentic marketing, brand fidelity becomes an <em>infrastructure</em> problem, not a guidelines problem.</blockquote>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<hr class="section-rule"/>

<section id="surfaces" class="section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="idx">§ 02 · Where your brand needs to live</div>
      <h2>One spec. <em>Three</em> places it gets read.</h2>
    </div>

    <p class="smallprint" style="margin-top:28px;max-width:62ch">
      Same file, different agents, different moments. Your BCP is designed to be consumed by your own team, across your vendor stack, and beyond your control. No rewriting for each audience.
    </p>

    <div class="surfaces">
      <div class="surface">
        <div class="num">Inside your team</div>
        <h3>Your <em>own</em> agents.</h3>
        <p>Copy, creative, media, compliance. The internal agent stack consumes <code>brand.md</code> to preserve senior-strategist judgment at machine scale. Every agent inherits the reflex on the first try.</p>
        <div class="examples">
          <span class="chip">copywriting</span>
          <span class="chip">creative gen</span>
          <span class="chip">media buying</span>
          <span class="chip">review and approval</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="surface">
        <div class="num">Across your partners</div>
        <h3>The <em>vendor</em> stack.</h3>
        <p>Zefr, Canva, Adobe, Meta, The Trade Desk, DSPs, creative-gen tools. Their agents read your <code>brand.md</code> to make better calls on your behalf. Faster onboarding, sharper classification, fewer brand-safety misses.</p>
        <div class="examples">
          <span class="chip">Zefr BSP</span>
          <span class="chip">Meta Advantage+</span>
          <span class="chip">Adobe GenStudio</span>
          <span class="chip">DSP briefs</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="surface">
        <div class="num">Beyond your control</div>
        <h3>The <em>consumer</em> agents.</h3>
        <p>ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity, Gemini, agentic storefronts. BCP is the first time you get <i>input</i> into how third-party consumer agents describe your brand. You get input, not control.</p>
        <div class="examples">
          <span class="chip">ChatGPT</span>
          <span class="chip">Perplexity</span>
          <span class="chip">Gemini</span>
          <span class="chip">agentic commerce</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="how" class="section" style="padding-top:0">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="idx">§ · How it works</div>
      <h2>Author once. <em>Publish</em>. Every agent reads it.</h2>
    </div>

    <ol class="steps">
      <li>
        <div class="step-n">01</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Author your <em>brand.md</em>.</h3>
          <p>Interview yourself with the free prompt, book an Expert Session, or commission a full Encoding Sprint. Output is a Git repo you own: <code>brand.md</code> plus six daughter files for voice, values, boundaries, claims, representation, and audiences.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="step-n">02</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Publish at <em>your domain</em>.</h3>
          <p>Host the files at <code>yourdomain.com/.well-known/brand.md</code>. Works on any static host: GitHub Pages, Cloudflare Pages, Vercel, Netlify, your own CDN. Ten-minute job for whoever ships your site.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="step-n">03</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Every agent <em>reads it</em>.</h3>
          <p>Internal copy agents, vendor platforms, consumer AIs. They fetch your BCP before they act. Your brand shows up to each one with exactly the context that task requires.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>

    <div style="margin-top:40px;display:flex;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap">
      <a class="btn accent-bg" href="/start">Start with the free prompt <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
      <a class="btn ghost" href="/docs">Read the spec</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="pricing" class="section" style="padding-top:0">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="idx">§ · Pricing</div>
      <h2>Three levels of depth, applied to <em>your brand</em>.</h2>
    </div>

    <p class="smallprint" style="margin-top:28px;max-width:62ch">
      Not three ways to get the same file. Three different degrees of strategic rigor. Pick the one that matches how load-bearing your brand is.
    </p>

    <div class="pricing">
      <div class="tier">
        <div class="tier-tag">Free</div>
        <div class="tier-price"><span class="num">$0</span><span class="per">your AI, your time</span></div>
        <h3>Self-authored.</h3>
        <p>Copy our prompt. Paste it into Claude, ChatGPT, Cowork, or Gemini. Answer the interview. You get a first-draft BCP in about 15 minutes. Honest about what it is: a strong draft, not a final product.</p>
        <ul class="tier-list">
          <li>The full authoring prompt, verbatim</li>
          <li>Seven markdown files you can publish today</li>
          <li>No signup, no account, no agency</li>
        </ul>
        <a class="btn ghost" href="/start">Copy the prompt <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
      </div>

      <div class="tier popular">
        <div class="tier-badge">Most popular</div>
        <div class="tier-tag">Expert Session</div>
        <div class="tier-price"><span class="num">$1,500</span><span class="per">90 minutes with a strategist</span></div>
        <h3>Structured, opinionated, reviewed.</h3>
        <p>Self-service run through our opinionated corpus, then a senior strategist reviews your draft, catches the gaps your AI missed, and sharpens voice, values, and boundaries. You leave with a BCP that's ready to ship.</p>
        <ul class="tier-list">
          <li>Our internal BCP authoring corpus</li>
          <li>90-minute review session, recorded</li>
          <li>One round of revisions on the output</li>
        </ul>
        <a class="btn accent-bg" href="mailto:hello@encodedbrands.com?subject=Expert%20Session%20-%20%241%2C500">Book an Expert Session <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
      </div>

      <div class="tier">
        <div class="tier-tag">Encoding Sprint</div>
        <div class="tier-price"><span class="num">$15,000</span><span class="per">one-week engagement</span></div>
        <h3>Senior judgment, applied.</h3>
        <p>A senior brand strategist takes your existing materials, interviews the people with the decisions in their heads, and writes a production BCP applied to your brand. The judgment an automated flow can't reach. Legal-reviewed claims, competitive positioning, platform-ready boundaries.</p>
        <ul class="tier-list">
          <li>Stakeholder interviews, positioning work</li>
          <li>Legal-reviewed claims and boundaries</li>
          <li>Launched on your domain, your repo</li>
        </ul>
        <a class="btn ghost" href="mailto:hello@encodedbrands.com?subject=Encoding%20Sprint%20-%20%2415K">Start a Sprint <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="smallprint" style="margin-top:28px;max-width:62ch">
      Enterprise engagements scale up from Sprint. <a href="mailto:hello@encodedbrands.com?subject=Enterprise" style="color:var(--accent)">Talk to us</a> if your brand is load-bearing on a ~nine-figure basis.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="protocol" class="section" style="padding-top:0">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="idx">§ · For the technically curious</div>
      <h2>It's <em>markdown</em>. Under version control. At a well-known path.</h2>
    </div>

    <p class="smallprint" style="margin-top:28px;max-width:62ch">
      The root file's YAML frontmatter, pulled live from our repo at build time. Same structure every BCP gets.
    </p>

    <aside class="dark-card" style="margin-top:36px" aria-label="Live brand.md frontmatter">
      <div class="dark-card-head">
        <span>encodedbrands.com/.well-known/brand.md</span>
        <span>live · pulled at build</span>
      </div>
      <pre>{brandYaml}</pre>
    </aside>

    <p class="smallprint" style="margin-top:28px;max-width:62ch">
      Spec under CC BY 4.0, reference code under MIT. <a href="/docs" style="color:var(--accent)">Read the full spec at /docs</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="manifesto">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow"><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>&nbsp;Manifesto</p>

    <div class="idx-grid" style="margin-top:36px">
      <div class="section-idx">§ · Manifesto</div>
      <div>
        <blockquote style="font-family:var(--serif);font-size:clamp(28px,3.2vw,44px);line-height:1.2;margin:0;font-style:italic">
          The brand deck <em>rotting</em> on a shared drive is the antagonist of this decade. Your agents can't read it. Your vendors won't. ChatGPT never will.
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="dogfood" class="section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="idx">§ · We use it ourselves</div>
      <h2>We <em>ship</em> our own brand as BCP.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="dogfood">
      <div class="dogfood-left">
        <div class="kicker">Reference implementation</div>
        <h3>Our brand is <em>a repo you can fork.</em></h3>
        <p>A brand consultancy that can't encode its own brand into BCP has a credibility problem. So we ship ours in public, at <b>encodedbrands.com/.well-known/brand.md</b>. It's the reference template every brand forks.</p>
        <p>The snippet on the right is pulled live from our <code>voice.md</code> at build. It's the same file our copy agents read before they write anything under the Encoded name.</p>
        <div class="meta">
          <span>License: <b>CC BY 4.0</b> (spec), <b>MIT</b> (code)</span>
          <span>Version: <b>0.1.0</b></span>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top:34px;display:flex;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap">
          <a class="btn" href="/.well-known/brand.md">Read our brand.md <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
          <a class="btn ghost" href="https://github.com/Bruiserhq/encodedbrands.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Fork the template</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="code-block" aria-label="voice.md preview, live">
        <div class="code-head">
          <span class="dots" aria-hidden="true"><i></i><i></i><i></i></span>
          <span>encoded / .well-known / brand / voice.md</span>
          <span>live</span>
        </div>
        <pre class="code-body">{voicePreview}</pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<hr class="section-rule"/>

<section id="launch" class="launch">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="idx-grid" style="align-items:baseline">
      <div class="section-idx">§ · Launch</div>
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow"><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>&nbsp;Now encoding founding brands</p>
        <h2>Author your BCP before <em>the category</em> authors it for you.</h2>
        <p>We're encoding a small cohort of founding brands. Live platform integrations, co-announcement at launch, logo rights, hosting, versioning, and founding-customer status on paid tiers.</p>
        <div class="cta-row">
          <a class="btn" href="mailto:hello@encodedbrands.com?subject=Founding%20brand%20partner">Become a founding partner <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
          <a class="btn ghost" href="/docs">Read the v0.1 spec</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .steps {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 56px 0 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 32px;
  }
  .steps li {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr;
    gap: 24px;
    align-items: start;
    padding: 28px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-soft);
  }
  .steps li:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-soft); }
  .step-n {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 14px;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .steps h3 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(22px, 2.2vw, 30px);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0 0 10px;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }
  .steps p { margin: 0; color: var(--ink-2); max-width: 60ch; }

  .pricing {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 20px;
    margin-top: 48px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .pricing { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .tier {
    position: relative;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-soft);
    padding: 28px 26px 32px;
    background: var(--paper);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  .tier.popular {
    border-color: var(--ink);
    background: var(--paper-2);
  }
  .tier-badge {
    position: absolute;
    top: -12px;
    left: 26px;
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--paper);
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 5px 10px;
  }
  .tier-tag {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .tier-price {
    margin: 14px 0 18px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .tier-price .num {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(34px, 3.6vw, 48px);
    line-height: 1;
  }
  .tier-price .per {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .tier h3 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2vw, 26px);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0 0 10px;
  }
  .tier p { color: var(--ink-2); margin: 0 0 16px; }
  .tier-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 22px;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--ink-2);
  }
  .tier-list li::before {
    content: "›";
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-right: 10px;
  }
  .tier .btn { margin-top: auto; justify-content: center; }
</style>
